def: One who, or that which, darkens.
The quality or condition of being illegal; unlawfulness; as,the illegality of trespass or of false imprisonment; also, an illegalact.
A chitinous membrane covering the exterior of many shells; --called also epidermis.
A Swedish coin worth about twenty-seven cents. It was formerlythe unit of value in Sweden.
A shingle; also, a slate for roofing. [Obs.] Holland.
To heat to excess; to superheat. Cowper.
To organic cohesion of different circled in a flower; adnation.
The apparatus used in Marconi wireless telegraphy.
Of or pertaining to an orator or to oratory; characterized byoratory; rhetorical; becoming to an orator; as, an oratoricaltriumph; an oratorical essay.-- Or`a*tor"ic*al*ly, adv.
Of or pertaining to the island anciently called Lesbos, nowMitylene, in the Grecian Archipelago.
A female slave, or one bound to service without wages, asdistinguished from a hired servant.
